definition: to emerge in large numbers/to spring up/to emerge prominently

sentences.english: Shocking, half known arms thrown around dreams.
sentences.chinese: 驚異的，半知曉的手臂湧現夢海。

sentences.english: Abundant church-creation is a blessing and a curse for the house-church movement, too.
sentences.chinese: 對於家庭教會來說，大量組織湧現是祝福也是詛咒。

sentences.english: From deep inside a bull- headed resolution welled up.
sentences.chinese: 一個固執的決定從內心深處湧現出來。

sentences.english: The runup in business school applications during the recession has created a windfall for essay writers.
sentences.chinese: 衰退期間湧現的商學院申請令論文寫手大發橫財。

sentences.english: Why is it that so often it's when we're in the middle of altercations that these sentiments come out?
sentences.chinese: 爲什麼常常是在爭吵中，這些情感才湧現出來呢？
全新的鄰里街坊湧現出來。

sentences.english: Where the darkness is thickest, there the bright beaming light that never is set is about to emerge.
sentences.chinese: 黑暗最濃重的時候，卻是光明即將湧現了。

sentences.english: The feelings emerge in the process of the poem, both in writing it and reading it.
sentences.chinese: 情感在整個詩歌過程都會湧現，無論是寫詩還是讀詩。

sentences.english: Great stories still flow but now there are smoothies in the picture.
sentences.chinese: 沒有咖啡仍然有好故事湧現，而且圖景更加柔順。

sentences.english: That the enemies sallied out was to be thought in his mind.
sentences.chinese: 敵人的突然湧現早在他的意料之中。

sentences.english: New cars come forth continuously mid and high-class cars meet a new inflexion?
sentences.chinese: 新車型不斷湧現中高級車迎來發展新拐點？

sentences.english: But even as some obstacles are removed, new ones spring up.
sentences.chinese: 但即使有些障礙已經被掃清，新的障礙還會湧現。

sentences.english: The young actress was the theatrical find of the year.
sentences.chinese: 這位年輕的女演員是那年戲劇界湧現出來的新秀。

sentences.english: At the same time, one of my good friend seems to have some few admirers.
sentences.chinese: 同一時間，身邊的一位好朋友的“桃花運”開始湧現。

sentences.english: Many new things are springing up.
Each kind of bad stimulation's emergence causes the college students' mental healthy crisis.
sentences.chinese: 各種劣性刺激的湧現導致大學生心理健康危機。
